commit.message: Replace two calls of gtk_container_add with gtk_button_set_image for compatibility with gtk2/3/(mostly)4

Render the LICENSE in the Help->About->License dialog
add gftp_get_doc_dir() / show AUTHORS file in About

gtk_image_new_from_stock is deprecated in newer versions of GTK.
Replace with gtk_image_new_from_icon_name() to remain forward compatible with gtk 3.10+
- Correct compilation error in update_file_status

src/gtk: now the new transfer GtkTreeView works

it's working but it's not finished

lib/protocol_ftp.c: fix segfault

was a typo

gftp-gtk.c: GTK3: hack to set a proper size for the log window

this is not a problem with gtk2, since everything is calculated automatically

gtk3: it looks like there is a problem with nested GtkPaned widgets

this is not a fix, it's an ugly hack, a proper fix must be devised one day

- Silence a few more compiler warnings

These are not strictly correct, but we were not handling possible
failures and examining ERRNO before anyway and these are calls that
should never really fail anyway so I think its ok to just silence
them any way that will appease the compiler.
